reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price!
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a small (smaller than a 1qt. ziplock bag) zippered pouch in my which I could carry a few large bandaids, 4-5 2x4 in. nonstick pads, the same number of 4x5 in. nonstick pads, a roll (flattened) of stretchy Coban type self adhesive bandage wrap, a small roll of good adhesive tape, a tube of triple antibiotic ointment, tweezers, nail clips, a needle (tip cork protected) for picking out thorns and splinters, a few packets of things such as acetaminophen, aspirin, antacid, and a small pair of scissors or alternately, a compact Swiss Army knife containing scissors. Also a few packets of salt which, dumped into a bottle of water, gives a serviceable makeshift saline solution to clean and rinse off a minor cut or scrape before bandaging. Just a little protective pouch, nylon, lightweight, with at least some internal organization dividers, ready to toss in a daypack or jacket pocket…and thus have at least something handy to deal with minor stuff. And one easily recognized for first aid in case it's my precious carcass I’ve injured and asked someone else to dig around in my pack. Is this the most rugged-duty, best-constructed pouch? Probably not…but it easily fulfills my needs and still has room to spare for additional items. Plus it comes as a twofer, for an incredible price! I couldn’t be happier!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent little bags
reviews.reviewText: Great value for two. The fabric seems to be decent, if anything crazy happens I'll update this in the future. Plenty of internal pockets/organization options as well. Only thing keeping this from a 5-star review is the zipper. Seems to get caught a lot when the pouch is empty/low but works better when it has items in it that fill/stuff it if that makes sense.

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I picked this coz it was a good price for 2 First Aid kit (bags only).I like the size. It’s perfect for traveling. It fit a lot of stuff inside… good for short trips.As soon as I got it I opened both… the red one was fine but I struggled to open the blue one. It seems the zippers is misaligned a bit.The exterior looks fine. There’s a minor imperfection on the red one.Interior: both red and blue interiors were poorly made. reviews.reviewText: I love these, not because they’re small, but it’s good that I have 2. I made one for work, since my workplace doesn’t have much stuff in theirs😒. El tamaño es apenas justo para mis necesidades, pero eso no es culpa del fabricante, cierra un poco "justo", razón por lo cual limita el contenidoSin embargo el verdadero problema es que el Zipper se atora al cerrar o abrir, sobretodo en la parte superior, parece que la esquina genera una resistencia al deslizamiento del Zipper, y esto se complica con una cantidad grande de restos de hilo que trae el producto, hilo sobrante de las costuras siguen ahí, hay que darse un tiempo y cortarlos con cuidado, la apariencia es de descuido
